🛡 Summary of Command Logic
* cat << 'EOF' > file: Creates/Overwrites a file with everything until it hits "EOF".
* cat << 'EOF' >> file: Appends to the end of an existing file.
* cat -: Tells a script to wait and read from the standard input (the pipe).

